  "text": "The functions h I (w; λ 1 , λ 2 ), with I = 1, . . . , 4, define maps from a local coordinate w into the sphere described with uniformizer z, and the primes denote derivatives with respect to w. An overline on an number denotes complex conjugation. We use a presentation of the moduli space in which (λ 1 , λ 2 ) = (x, y), where ξ = x + iy is the position of the moving puncture. It is then possible to rewrite the relevant two-form as [CITATION_1] ",
